# Tactile Digital Design System

This project follows a "tactile digital" design philosophy that rejects cold, flat aesthetics in favor of warm, human, and grounded design elements.

## Core Design Principles

### 1. Human-Centered Aesthetics
- **Reject**: Sharp corners, perfect geometric shapes, cold colors
- **Embrace**: Organic shapes, warm colors, imperfect but intentional asymmetry
- **Goal**: Create digital experiences that feel physical and approachable

### 2. Typography Hierarchy
- **Headlines**: Use `font-headline` (Playfair Display) for all h1-h6 elements
- **Body Text**: Use `font-body` (Inter) for paragraphs, buttons, inputs, and UI text
- **Never**: Mix serif and sans-serif inappropriately
- **Always**: Maintain clear hierarchy with headline fonts for emphasis

### 3. Color Philosophy
- **Primary Palette**: 
  - `bg-parchment` (#F8F5EE) - Warm, paper-like background
  - `text-charcoal` (#2B2A2D) - Rich, deep text color
  - `bg-terracotta` (#D98666) - Warm accent for CTAs
  - `bg-sage` (#88A89A) - Subtle secondary accent
- **Usage**: Colors should evoke natural materials (paper, clay, stone)

### 4. Shape Language
- **Default Border Radius**: Use custom squircle variations instead of standard rounded corners
  - `rounded-squircle` - Primary asymmetric shape (2rem 1rem 1rem 2rem)
  - `rounded-squircle-sm` - Smaller elements (1.5rem 0.75rem 0.75rem 1.5rem)
  - `rounded-squircle-lg` - Large elements (2.5rem 1.25rem 1.25rem 2.5rem)
  - `rounded-squircle-alt` - Alternative shape (1rem 2rem 2rem 1rem)
- **Avoid**: Perfect circles (`rounded-full`) and standard rectangles (`rounded-lg`)

### 5. Depth and Texture
- **Shadows**: Always use paper-like shadows (`shadow-paper`, `shadow-paper-lg`, `shadow-paper-xl`)
- **Texture**: Apply `bg-grain` to main backgrounds for subtle texture
- **Layering**: Use `paper-texture` class for enhanced tactile feel on cards

## Component Standards

### Cards
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - Tactile card with organic shape and depth
<div className="tactile-card paper-texture p-8">
  <h2 className="font-headline text-charcoal">Card Title</h2>
  <p className="font-body text-charcoal/80">Card content</p>
</div>

// ❌ Wrong - Generic card without tactile qualities
<div className="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8">
  <h2>Card Title</h2>
  <p>Card content</p>
</div>
```

### Buttons
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - Tactile buttons with proper styling
<button className="tactile-button">Primary Action</button>
<button className="tactile-button-secondary">Secondary Action</button>

// ❌ Wrong - Generic button without tactile qualities
<button className="bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-md px-4 py-2">
  Button
</button>
```

### Form Inputs
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - Tactile input with organic shape
<input className="tactile-input" placeholder="Enter text..." />

// ❌ Wrong - Standard input without tactile qualities
<input className="border rounded-md px-3 py-2" />
```

